1. Start by opening the code and doing a bit of first glance inspection.
2. The first thing that is easy to see is that the password must be 12 chars in length.
3. Second, it is split into three slices of 4 chars.
4. Then, some XORs are performed on the blocks.
5. Copy the part that crafts the final string into a js interpreter, have it print the crafted string instead of comparing with the hardcoded value, and pass the hardcoded value to it.
6. Plug the result in the curl -> flag.
